A 26-year-old man, Kelechi Emeka, on Thursday appeared before an Ikorodu Magistrates’ Court in Lagos State for allegedly assaulting a police officer performing his lawful duty. Emeka, whose address was not provided, is facing a charge of assault to which he pleaded not guilty. The Prosecutor, Sgt. Mary Ajiteru told the court that the defendant committed the offences on January 29 at about 9:00 a.m. at Kokoro Abu along Sabo Road, Ikorodu. ALSO READ:S/East govs back community policing, Ohanaeze Ndigbo wants FG to brand herdsmen as terrorists Congestion: Maersk Line, Safmarine deny dumping Lagos ports Reps place YABATECH on status enquiry over unaudited… Okada, tricycle restrictions: Security outweighs convenience… Sanwo-Olu inducts 1017 officers into LASTMA Ajiteru said that the defendant assaulted the complainant, Insp. Babatunde Kadiri, by dragging him around for asking him to obey the traffic rules. Ajiteru said that the offences contravened Section 172 of Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015. The Magistrate, Mrs Tunji-Careena, granted the defendant bail in the sum of N50, 000 with one surety in like sum. Tunji-Careena adjourned the case until February 20 for mention. NAN SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE TO GET IT!!! STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY INTO YOUR SPECIFIED BANK ACCOUNT.REGISTRATION IS ABSOLUTELY FREE.